From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 04:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Input: rotary-encoder - fall back to fwnode_irq_get when
 gpiod_to_irq fails

Some gpiochips (e.g. Amlogic Meson) don't implement the `.to_irq`
callback, so gpiod_to_irq() returns -ENXIO for every GPIO and the
rotary-encoder driver fails probe with "unable to request IRQ -6".

Fall back to fwnode_irq_get(dev_fwnode(dev), i) when gpiod_to_irq
fails so boards can wire IRQs explicitly via "interrupts" or
"interrupts-extended" - entries in those properties are matched
positionally against the entries in "gpios".

When the IRQ comes from DT, drop the IRQF_TRIGGER_RISING/FALLING
flags from request_threaded_irq - the trigger type is already set
on the IRQ via the DT cells, and forcing EDGE_BOTH overrides it.
That override fails on IRQ controllers that don't support edge-both
(e.g. Amlogic G12A gpio_intc returns -EINVAL from .irq_set_type).

The check is done via a signed local because struct rotary_encoder.irq
is `unsigned int *`; comparing `encoder->irq[i] < 0` would silently fold
to false on the unsigned cast and miss the gpiod_to_irq error.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
diff --git a/drivers/input/misc/rotary_encoder.c b/drivers/input/misc/rotary_encoder.c
index f706e1997..7ab01c208 100644
--- a/drivers/input/misc/rotary_encoder.c
+++ b/drivers/input/misc/rotary_encoder.c
@@ -277,12 +277,35 @@ static int rotary_encoder_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return -ENOMEM;

 	for (i = 0; i < encoder->gpios->ndescs; ++i) {
-		encoder->irq[i] = gpiod_to_irq(encoder->gpios->desc[i]);
+		unsigned long irqflags = IRQF_ONESHOT;
+		int irq = gpiod_to_irq(encoder->gpios->desc[i]);
+
+		if (irq < 0) {
+			/*
+			 * Some gpiochips (e.g. Amlogic Meson) don't implement
+			 * .to_irq, so gpiod_to_irq() returns -ENXIO. Allow
+			 * boards to wire IRQs explicitly via the device's
+			 * "interrupts"/"interrupts-extended" properties; the
+			 * indices match the order of "gpios". When the IRQ
+			 * came from DT, trust the trigger type already set
+			 * via the interrupts cells - forcing EDGE_BOTH here
+			 * would override that and fails on IRQ controllers
+			 * that don't support edge-both (e.g. Amlogic G12A).
+			 */
+			irq = fwnode_irq_get(dev_fwnode(dev), i);
+			if (irq < 0) {
+				dev_err(dev, "no IRQ available for gpio#%d\n",
+					i);
+				return irq;
+			}
+		} else {
+			irqflags |= IRQF_TRIGGER_RISING |
+				    IRQF_TRIGGER_FALLING;
+		}
+		encoder->irq[i] = irq;

 		err = devm_request_threaded_irq(dev, encoder->irq[i],
-				NULL, handler,
-				IRQF_TRIGGER_RISING | IRQF_TRIGGER_FALLING |
-				IRQF_ONESHOT,
+				NULL, handler, irqflags,
 				DRV_NAME, encoder);
 		if (err) {
 			dev_err(dev, "unable to request IRQ %d (gpio#%d)\n",
